<subSubSection id="7E0D10A3575AC29CA8C22EA9863C1CFA" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph id="68D05FED8441281066920CEEFDDC3E8F" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B47AB32BBC99FFF0F329DE1ADDF0594" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall dark brown. Pronotal disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="635CDC1AC1853A35101238FE04B302A5" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8F</figureCitation>
) dark brown, lacking vittae, pronotal expansions almost entirely pale yellow dark brown, except by posterior margin, which is outlined in brown, blending with the dark brown disc color. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A8DF62E631FA45361421778CA5D2DFDC" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8A, C</figureCitation>
) dark brown or brown, with a pale-yellow longitudinal stripe about as long as 3/5
<normalizedToken id="16DAA03E3177D3FE9C6329B158D4CF9E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
elytral length. Legs (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CDADFB65A9BA5341DB5D08147ADD2879" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8B-D</figureCitation>
) dark brown, except for trochanters, which are light brown. Sternum VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1E1B223CFFE640D6E49DAF2391378B2A" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8G</figureCitation>
) with lateral vitreous spots. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EC28DFBDD76192B6BA48D64EAA962171" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8H</figureCitation>
) entirely brown.
</paragraph>
