<paragraph id="0DE35B849D9D0A478F6857163720C866" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="003AA6B53A6712FABDB94AB8BC4F9870" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8F</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, divergent posteriorly. 
<emphasis id="EC2FB24DE8AAE279F7DED0E76599361E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Total length = 7.3-8.1 mm (aver. 7.7 mm); Pronotal length = 1.6-1.8 mm (aver. 1.7 mm); Pronotal width = 2.4-2.6 mm (aver. 2.5 mm); Elytral length = 5.8-6.0 mm (aver. 5.9 mm); Elytral width = 1.5-1.6 mm (aver. 1.55 mm). Antennomere III (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="502898BB278EE86040119FD66FD21EC5" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8E</figureCitation>
) with lamella almost 3
<normalizedToken id="683FCFD61894A61F7093BEC249B39E05" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than core antennomere. Sternum VI (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="83DF323B3AA9F82F7C04F522540EC212" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8B, G</figureCitation>
) with a lantern of moderate size, occupying the medial 1.4 of the sternum, reaching its anterior margin. Sternum VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B76B7F504203E4543DD13588967EC16E" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8G</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin bisinuose. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="234531CF70F9CCD2C35BB5C6ACCA6588" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8H</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, posterior corners barely visible, posterior margin rounded. Syntergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B2D76CEA9E4CA2784BD3B0904955AFA0" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8I, J</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin mildly curved. Phallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="614BC5C99FECD2D3753332E6D52CD35F" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8K-M</figureCitation>
) with dorsal plate almost straight in lateral view, with sides straight and acuminate at apical half. Paramere apex curved ventrally, ventral projection (lateral view) inconspicuous. 
<emphasis id="F69E678DE558AC46EDDDF52DA677F537" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D141FEDC8BA0CCED68BCACDE8DC0C0A4" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8C, D</figureCitation>
). Total length = 8.3-8.7 mm (aver. 8.5 mm); Pronotal length = 1.6-1.8 mm (aver. 1.7 mm); Pronotal width = 2.5-2.7 mm (aver. 2.6 mm); Elytral length = 6.2-6.6 mm (aver. 6.5 mm); Elytral width = 1.9-2.0 mm (aver. 1.95 mm). Antennomeres III-X with apical corners projected, pointed, Sternum VI (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EEC3BA48B659DA356C865FB5A85FC8CB" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Costalampys capixaba sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543211" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">8D</figureCitation>
) with a small lantern, occupying the medial 1/6 of the sternum, reaching its anterior margin.
</paragraph>
